title: Summertime
lyrics:
I don't know why, but this feels like summer time
I laid at night, this feels turning at my side
Maybe it's the lights, or the walk just in our mids
I don't know why, but this feels like summer time
When I catch you alone, just you and me

Make you my own, you're all I need

I'm here alone, just here for you

Make you my own, you feel all the time



We can go to my place, till' the fall lies

No need for phone calls

Yeah, we can kill time

You know what you want, I know what I need

You want a good time

Girl, you can trust me



I don't know why



I don't know why it feels like paradise

Think at your eyes, [?]

This was the night, and we're running out of time

I don't know why but you look like paradise



When I catch you alone, just you and me

Make you my own, you're all I need

I'm here alone, just here for you

Make you my own, you feel all the time



We can go to my place, till' the fall lies

No need for phone calls

Yeah, we can kill time

You know what you want, I know what I need

You want a good time

Girl, you can trust me



I don't know why
